data.enText: a metal that is formed by mixing two types of metal together, or by mixing metal with another substance
Brass is an alloy of copper and zinc.

data.chText: 把…铸成合金（尤指掺入一种价值低的金属）
data.enText: to mix one metal with another, especially one of lower value

means: 把…铸成合金(尤指掺入一种价值低的金属)

tr: the state of impairing the quality or reducing the value of something
a mixture containing two or more metallic elements or metallic and nonmetallic elements usually fused together or dissolving into each other when molten
example: brass is an alloy of zinc and copper

tr: lower in value by increasing the base-metal content

value.def: An alloy is a metal that is made by mixing two or more types of metal together.

example.ex: Bronze is an alloy of copper and tin...
